IDB Approves Loans of $511 Million to Five Countries, SPA Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-03-01T12:33:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/idb-approves-loans-of-511-million-to-five-countries-spa-says.html
The board of the  Islamic Development
Bank , a Saudi Arabia-based multilateral lender, approved loans
totaling $511 million to finance projects in five countries, the
 Saudi Press Agency  reported, citing the bank.  The projects include building a highway in Albania,
developing vocational schools in  Turkey , constructing steel
silos to store grain in  Pakistan  and supplying water to the
Yemeni capital Sanaâ€™a, the news service said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
